{
  "stem": "15962.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that was done primarily by Josef Mengele, that would-- people would strip and had to walk in front of him, and he would decide whether they were good candidates for-- for work.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I was a child then.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the camp started emptying out, first men and then women.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother volunteered for work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father couldn't because he was not only too old, but by that time he was really very ill, and was in a block, in a barrack, for sick people.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I occasionally came to see him, and was shocked at his-- his condition and his resignation that he will not survive.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, some semblance of whatever we-- I mean, we never-- they never replenished.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] But essentially, us children had our old clothes that we brought with us a year earlier.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, until then, my-- even though I did not see my parents daily, the feeling that we were all in the same camp did give children some support, some feeling of quasi security.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] of course, there was very little that we could decide or-- or make choices of our free will.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was, as I said, day to day matter of living through the day, and hoping for a little piece of bread with a-- with a square of margarine in the evening, which was the main food ration that we got.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Got some watered down black coffee in the morning, and a-- a watery soup at lunchtime, and that was all we would get.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So those were the kind of main events, because hunger by then was a gnawing, very-- very debilitating feeling all the time.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And as children, we-- I believe we got slightly better food.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
